36:58.633 --> 37:01.546
♪ Ding, ding, dong ♪

37:12.188 --> 37:13.395
Ma'am?

37:15.191 --> 37:17.649
Excuse me, ma'am.
Ma'am.

37:46.014 --> 37:49.678
I can only imagine
how you must be feeling, but...

37:49.809 --> 37:52.517
let me assure you that the
disinterment was unfortunate,

37:52.645 --> 37:54.352
but necessary, Mrs. Zweig.

37:56.399 --> 37:57.731
Hmm.

38:00.528 --> 38:03.521
I read about
the boy on the bridge.

38:06.701 --> 38:08.784
About what he was wearing.

38:10.830 --> 38:13.493
Your son's desire to wear
the same clothing as his sister

38:13.625 --> 38:16.038
has little in common
with the boy on the bridge.

38:16.169 --> 38:18.752
You said there was
no need for concern.

38:21.800 --> 38:25.794
You said our acceptance of
Benjamin was what mattered most.

38:29.849 --> 38:32.683
And we believed you.

38:32.811 --> 38:34.643
We trusted you.

38:38.650 --> 38:40.232
Giorgio Santorelli
dressed as he did

38:40.360 --> 38:42.693
because he was a prostitute.

38:42.821 --> 38:45.313
Benjamin was only following
his nature.

38:51.996 --> 38:53.703
Mrs. Zweig...

38:54.999 --> 38:58.163
...your son was the victim
of a very disturbed mind.

39:02.966 --> 39:04.958
My Benjamin is dead.

39:09.389 --> 39:12.803
Both my children are dead.

39:14.978 --> 39:16.844
Because of you.

39:52.348 --> 39:54.135
Gentlemen,
this is John Moore,

39:54.267 --> 39:55.508
a friend and colleague.

39:55.643 --> 39:57.883
Hello, Mr. Moore. I'm Detective
Sergeant Marcus Isaacson.

39:57.979 --> 39:59.060
This is my brother, Lucius.

39:59.188 --> 40:01.805
Detective Sergeant
Lucius Isaacson.

40:01.941 --> 40:03.544
Theodore didn't trust
the coroner's office

40:03.568 --> 40:06.356
to keep silent about
revisiting the Zweig case.

40:06.487 --> 40:08.979
It was good of Commissioner
Roosevelt to lend you to us.

40:09.115 --> 40:11.903
May I ask how long we have
the benefit of your expertise?

40:12.035 --> 40:13.321
As long as you like, Doctor.

40:13.453 --> 40:15.806
I doubt my brother and I will be
missed at the police department.

40:15.830 --> 40:19.665
I imagine your modern methods
don't make you very popular.

40:19.792 --> 40:21.033
That and the fact we're Jews.

40:22.045 --> 40:24.378
Has the commissioner told you
what this is about?

40:24.505 --> 40:26.292
Only that we're to perform
an autopsy

40:26.424 --> 40:28.416
and keep the results
strictly confidential.

40:29.886 --> 40:32.924
Benjamin and Sofia Zweig.
Their bodies were discovered...

40:33.056 --> 40:35.056
Three years ago in a water tower
on Suffolk Street.

40:35.183 --> 40:37.300
- We read the file.
- The injuries to the boy

40:37.435 --> 40:39.552
are what interests me
the most.

40:45.193 --> 40:47.810
You've heard about the
Santorelli murder, I assume?

40:47.946 --> 40:49.357
Of course.

40:50.615 --> 40:51.967
If you're looking
for similarities,

40:51.991 --> 40:54.261
there's only so much we can tell
from a body in this state.

40:54.285 --> 40:57.449
I want you to look at
what remains...

40:57.580 --> 41:01.290
each bone, each fragment
for every detail, every mark,

41:01.417 --> 41:03.750
no matter how insignificant.

41:05.630 --> 41:07.838
Anything that may connect
Benjamin Zweig

41:07.966 --> 41:09.377
to the Santorelli boy.

41:09.509 --> 41:11.671
We will do our best, Doctor.

41:17.433 --> 41:20.642
Get the "Tribune"!
Get the "Tribune"!

41:21.688 --> 41:23.896
Get the "Tribune"!
Get the "Tribune"!

41:24.023 --> 41:26.231
They won't be finished
for quite some time.

41:26.359 --> 41:28.521
I thought we might get
an early dinner somewhere.

41:28.653 --> 41:30.610
How can you think
of eating now?

41:30.738 --> 41:33.105
I don't recall you being
so delicate.

41:33.241 --> 41:34.698
I'm afraid once seen,

41:34.826 --> 41:37.614
those images
will remain forever in my head.

41:39.205 --> 41:42.539
That's what I admire
about you, John.

41:42.667 --> 41:44.829
You represent the good
that people want to believe

41:44.961 --> 41:46.372
is in all of us.

41:46.504 --> 41:49.121
It's why people like you more
than they do me.

42:07.316 --> 42:08.523
Thank you, Cyrus.

42:22.665 --> 42:24.657
Get the "Tribune"!
Get the "Tribune"!

42:31.799 --> 42:33.210
Come!

42:37.180 --> 42:38.762
- Cyrus!
- Sir?

42:38.890 --> 42:40.492
Were you away from the carriage
at any point?

42:40.516 --> 42:42.553
No, sir.

42:42.685 --> 42:44.768
What?
Do you see something?

42:57.867 --> 42:59.483
There.

43:01.662 --> 43:03.870
Laszlo!

43:09.504 --> 43:10.585
Laszlo!

43:55.007 --> 43:56.839
Laszlo!

44:50.271 --> 44:51.512
Laszlo!

45:38.986 --> 45:40.318
Laszlo!

45:47.286 --> 45:48.697
Where did he go?

46:06.764 --> 46:09.302
Did you see
the Santorelli boy's mouth?

46:22.029 --> 46:23.861
I'm certain
cold-blooded killers

46:23.990 --> 46:24.990
walk among us.

46:29.328 --> 46:32.071
They're out there now, hidden,

46:32.206 --> 46:34.368
yet their motives
are understandable,

46:34.500 --> 46:37.459
but this one is different.

46:38.754 --> 46:41.497
His acts are so wretched,
so evil that...

46:42.508 --> 46:45.717
...only if I become him,

46:45.845 --> 46:48.508
if I cut
the child's throat myself...

46:50.266 --> 46:52.383
...if I run my knife
through the helpless body

46:52.518 --> 46:55.181
and pluck innocent eyes
from a horrified face...

46:56.522 --> 47:00.266
...only then will I come
to truly understand what I am.

47:00.401 --> 47:02.688
Only then will I recognize
that what drives me

47:02.820 --> 47:05.813
is not an absence of emotion
at all.

47:05.948 --> 47:08.361
Rather, a torrent of feeling.

47:08.492 --> 47:10.028
The kind that gives meaning
and purpose

47:10.161 --> 47:11.868
to my own blackened soul.

47:13.831 --> 47:16.744
I must see life
as he sees it.

47:17.752 --> 47:20.244
Feel pain as he feels it.

47:21.297 --> 47:24.210
Take the same path he takes.

47:24.342 --> 47:25.753
Yes.

47:25.885 --> 47:28.093
I must follow this
wherever it goes.

47:29.847 --> 47:33.591
Even if it leads me
to the darkest pit of hell.

47:40.358 --> 47:42.020
What's wrong, child?

